## Test Anti-Pattern Audit

**Summary: 3 Critical · 2 High · 2 Medium · 2 Low**

This class is very likely the root cause of your incident. 4 of 8 tests will pass regardless of whether the code works correctly.

---

### 🔴 Critical — False Confidence

**1. No assertion — `GetUser_NonExistentId_ReturnsNull`**

The test retrieves a user and does nothing with it. It always passes.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
var user = repo.GetById(999);
// should be null

// ✅ Fix
var user = repo.GetById(999);
Assert.IsNull(user);
```

**2. Swallowed exception — `AddUser_DuplicateId_ThrowsException`**

If no exception is thrown, the test silently passes (falls off the end of `try`). The `catch` also swallows — so it passes either way.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
try {
    repo.Add(new User(1, "Bob"));
} catch (Exception) {
    return; // test passes
}

// ✅ Fix — replace entire body after first Add
Assert.ThrowsException<InvalidOperationException>(() => repo.Add(new User(1, "Bob")));
```

**3. Always-true assertion — `DeleteUser_RemovesFromRepository`**

`Assert.AreEqual(repo.Count, repo.Count)` compares the value to itself. This can never fail.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
Assert.AreEqual(repo.Count, repo.Count);

// ✅ Fix
Assert.AreEqual(0, repo.Count);
```

---

### 🟠 High

**4. Broad exception type — `AddUser_NullUser_ThrowsArgumentNullException`**

Asserts `Exception` but the method throws `ArgumentNullException`. This would also pass on any unrelated crash. The test name even says the right type.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
Assert.ThrowsException<Exception>(() => repo.Add(null!));

// ✅ Fix
Assert.ThrowsException<ArgumentNullException>(() => repo.Add(null!));
```

**5. Weak assertion — `UpdateUser_ChangesName`**

`user.Name != "Alice"` would pass if the name were `""`, `null`, or any garbage. Assert what it *should* be.

```csharp
// ❌ Before
Assert.IsTrue(user.Name != "Alice");

// ✅ Fix
Assert.AreEqual("Alicia", user.Name);
```

---

### 🟡 Medium / 🟢 Low

| Severity | Test | Issue |
|----------|------|-------|
| Medium | `GetUser_ExistingId_ReturnsUser` | Only asserts `IsNotNull` — doesn't verify `Id` or `Name`. Add `Assert.AreEqual("Alice", user.Name);` |
| Medium | `SearchUsers_ByPartialName_FindsMatches` | `Assert.IsTrue(results.Count == 2)` — use `Assert.AreEqual(2, results.Count)` for better failure messages |
| Low | Class field | `_client` (`HttpClient`) is never used and never disposed — remove it |
| Low | `SearchUsers_ByPartialName_FindsMatches` | Leftover `Console.WriteLine` — remove |

---

### ✅ Positive Observations

- **`GetAllUsers_ReturnsCorrectCount`** is well-written: verifies count *and* content
- **Naming convention** is consistent (`Method_Scenario_Expected`) across the class
- **Test isolation** is good — each test creates its own `UserRepository` instance, no shared mutable state

---

### Priority

Fix the 3 Critical issues **immediately** — they are almost certainly masking bugs in production today. The High issues should follow right after. The rest can be addressed opportunistically.
